TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Strategy Which Maximizes the Geometric Mean Return on Portfolio Investments
AU  - Vander Weide, James H.
AU  - Peterson, David W.
AU  - Maier, Steven F.
Y1  - 1977/06/01
PY  - 1977
DA  - 1977/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.23.10.1117
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.23.10.1117
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1117
EP  - 1123
VL  - 23
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A common formulation of the portfolio selection problem leads to the prescription of a strategy which maximizes the geometric mean return on investments. In this paper we examine conditions under which solutions exist for the case where the returns distribution is discrete. We establish necessary and sufficient conditions for a solution to exist and give a computationally convenient and exact method for finding a solution in circumstances where (i) a solution exists and (ii) the number of securities equals or exceeds the number of values in the returns distribution.
AB  - A common formulation of the portfolio selection problem leads to the prescription of a strategy which maximizes the geometric mean return on investments. In this paper we examine conditions under which solutions exist for the case where the returns distribution is discrete. We establish necessary and sufficient conditions for a solution to exist and give a computationally convenient and exact method for finding a solution in circumstances where (i) a solution exists and (ii) the number of securities equals or exceeds the number of values in the returns distribution.
